-- Corning sees capital expenditures up to $1.7 billion
-- 
-- Wed Dec 5, 2007 5:27pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/05/us-corning-outlook-idUSWNAS385320071205

 

 SAN FRANCISCO  (Reuters) - Corning Inc ( GLW.N ) said on Wednesday it expects 2008 capital expenditures ranging from $1.5 billion to $1.7 billion as the company prepares to meet growing demand for large flat-panel televisions. 

 The expenditures, higher than in 2007, include $400 million for a new production facility in Japan. Corning said it expects expenditures in its display business to range from $800 million to $1 billion. (Reporting by  Philipp Gollner ; editing by Carol Bishopric)